I enjoyed a lot the different sonification methods presented in this study. Most of them were super relaxing. However, I wonder how hard could be for a person to recognize the information encoded in the tracks, specially when more than two events happen at the same time.
I think the sound of water is not appropriate, for it makes it difficult to distinguish the changes. Moreover, we are used to the sound of nature and it attracts less reflection from our brain.

I belive the sofinication can be offered in 3 different packages. What I found annouying for me at night was pleasent in morning. Therefore, it would be nice to give different offers for different type of peopel. Good luck!
I found the natural sounds better for the base line signals, and the unnatural sounds like bell better for the threshold exceeding signals.
